OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBahrain activist gets      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fapology for Gatwick        
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fdetention                  
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The Home Office has apologised to a    
OL,6, human-rights activist held at Gatwick  
OL,7, Airport by the Border Force.           
OL,9,FSayed Ahmed Alwadei, who campaigns for 
OL,10,Fhuman rights in Bahrain, was detained  
OL,11,Ffor two and a half hours in September  
OL,12,F2023, after returning from Geneva.     
OL,14,FMr Alwadei, a refugee who has          
OL,15,Findefinite leave to remain in the UK,  
OL,16,Fwas told by Home Office lawyers he had 
OL,17,Fbeen "unlawfully detained".            
OL,19,FThe Home Office said it could not      
OL,20,Fcomment on individual cases.           
